  "updated_summary": "American Express's success is attributed to its quality compounding, steady business, and growing revenues, with earnings in the low double digits, as noted by Lisa Ellis. Dominick Gabriele highlighted the company's strong comeback post-COVID and diversified business model. The company's origins trace back to 1850 as a freight forwarding business, as evidenced by archival footage of a train car labeled 'Shipped by AMERICAN EXPRESS International Freight,' and text overlays indicating 'Closed-loop system,' 'Revenue model,' and 'Future.' It later transformed into a payments company in the late 19th century, introducing financial products and travel services, with Benji Stawski noting the introduction of its first charge card in the 1950s, following the success of traveler checks, to provide a more convenient payment method. A modern American Express card, including the gold 'Centurion' card, represents the brand as it is known today. The company operates a closed-loop system, where American Express acts as the issuer, acquirer, and network, contrasting with open-loop systems used by Visa and Mastercard where separate banks are involved. This closed-loop structure allows American Express to gather detailed customer spending data, enabling targeted advertising and rewards, unlike Visa and Mastercard, which only see total dollar amounts. Doug Kantor of the Merchant Payments Coalition explained that this system allows Amex to tailor deals for merchants without bank interference, a flexibility not available to Visa and Mastercard. The closed-loop system also enables Amex to earn interest income, generating $9.9 billion in 2022, and significant discount revenues from merchants, exceeding $30 billion in 2022, which constitutes over 58% of its total revenue. Merchants are willing to pay a premium for Amex because it attracts affluent, high-spending customers, who spend three times more annually than average cardholders. Amex targets these affluent cardholders through a spend-centric model, offering premium products like the Amex Platinum card with travel benefits, rewards, and airport lounge access, supported by a $17 billion investment in services and rewards in 2022."
